'''Graduate Medical Education''' ('''GME''') refers to any type of formal medical education, usually hospital-sponsored or hospital-based training, pursued after receipt of the [[Doctor of Medicine|M.D.]] or [[Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine|D.O.]] degree in the [[United States]] This education includes [[internship (medicine)|internship]], [[residency (medicine)|residency]], subspecialty and fellowship programs, and leads to state licensure and board certification.<ref>[http://www.ama-assn.org/ama/pub/education-careers/graduate-medical-education.page Graduate Medical Education (American Medical Association)]</ref><ref>[http://www.osteopathic.org/inside-aoa/Education/OGME-development-initiative/Pages/what-is-osteopathic-graduate-medical-education.aspx What is Osteopathic Graduate Medical Education]</ref>

