'''Kumdang-2''' is an alleged cure for [[AIDS]], [[Ebola virus|Ebola]], [[MERS]] and [[tuberculosis]] created in [[North Korea]].<ref>{{cite web|title=North Korea says it has 'cure' for MERS, Ebola, AIDS|url=https://news.yahoo.com/north-korea-says-cure-mers-ebola-aids-153805355.html|publisher=''Yahoo News!''|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref> According to the website Minjok Tongshin, a version of the drug was originally produced in 1996.<ref name="hp">{{cite news|title=North Korea Claims It Has Found Cure For MERS, Ebola, SARS And AIDS|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/06/19/north-korea-cure-mers_n_7620590.html|accessdate=16 March 2017|work=Huffington Post|date=19 June 2015}}</ref> The name means "golden sugar" in Korean.<ref>{{cite web|title=North Korea claims it can cure MERS (and a whole bunch of other things)|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/worldviews/wp/2015/06/19/north-korea-claims-it-can-cure-mers-and-a-whole-bunch-of-other-things/|publisher=''The Washington Post''|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref>

It is manufactured by the [[Pugang Pharmaceutical Company]].<ref>[http://www.kcna.co.jp/item/2015/201506/news18/20150618-26ee.html Kumdang-2 Injection] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620224217/http://www.kcna.co.jp/item/2015/201506/news18/20150618-26ee.html |date=2015-06-20 }}, KCNA, 18 June 2015.</ref> According to the [[Korean Central News Agency]], the drug's ingredients include [[ginseng]], small amounts of rare earth metals<ref>{{cite web | url=http://kumdang2.com/dosing-and-treatment-course/ | title=Manufactor Website | accessdate=19 June 2015 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620160018/http://kumdang2.com/dosing-and-treatment-course/ | archivedate=20 June 2015 | df= }}</ref> and trace amounts of [[gold]] and [[platinum]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jun/19/north-korea-cure-mers-aids-ebola-vaccine | title=North Korea claims 'cure' for Mers, Aids and Ebola | work=The Guardian | date=19 June 2015 | accessdate=19 June 2015 | author=Associated Press}}</ref> According to the KCNA, it can also cure cancer, morning sickness, and "harm from the use of computers".<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-06-20/north-korea-says-it-has-cure-for-mers-aids-ebola/6560406 North Korea claims Kumdang-2 vaccine cures MERS, AIDS, Ebola and "harm from the use of computers"], ABC, 20 June 2015.</ref> The drug was mentioned during deadly [[Avian influenza|bird flu]] outbreaks in 2006 and 2013.<ref name="hp"/>

