The '''Orthotic Prosthetic Center (OPC)''' is a family owned and operated [[prosthetics]] lab with offices in [[Fairfax, Virginia]] and Rockville, Maryland. The company is also featured on ''[[Rebuilt: The Human Body Shop]]'', a [[reality television|reality TV show]] that debuted in January 2006 on the [[Discovery Health Channel]]. OPC was founded in 1980 by Joan Weintrob who was the first woman in the U.S. to earn an orthotics and prosthetics certification from the [[American Board for Certification]].{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}

