'''Pauline Chaponnière-Chaix''' ([[Geneva]], 1 November 1850 – Geneva, 6 December 1934) was a Swiss nurse, feminist and [[suffragette]]. She was one of four employees of the [[International Committee of the Red Cross]] after [[World War I]],<ref name="FehrenbachRodogno2015">{{cite book|author1=Heide Fehrenbach|author2=Davide Rodogno|title=Humanitarian Photography|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bBZoBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA164|date=23 February 2015|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-107-06470-6|pages=164–}}</ref> and served as president of the [[International Council of Women]] during the period of 1920-22.{{sfn|Janz|Schönpflug|2014|p=51}}

